    description:   'One of the shortest walks to UMass on this list, at one of the lowest price points — the reason it stays almost entirely student-occupied year after year.\n\n🏠 The Community\nThe tenant base is dominated by students, with a steady trickle of young professionals filling in around them. The atmosphere is friendly and low-drama — neighbours keep to themselves but the halls aren\'t empty. Units are older but well looked after, and the community feel benefits from the fact that everyone here is roughly in the same life stage.\n\n💡 What\'s Included\nKitchens come equipped to standard, with surface parking available and shared on-site laundry. Only one layout is offered — a 2 Bed / 1 Bath at 650 sqft — so figure out your roommate situation before applying. Heat and electricity are on the tenant.\n\n🚌 Getting Around\nAbout a 10-minute walk to UMass campus, with PVTA Routes 30 and 31 serving the area as a backup in bad weather. The real locational advantage is that the on-site Indian grocery store, Crestview Plaza, and House of Teriyaki are all within the same short walk — a combination that\'s hard to find elsewhere near campus and makes this a favourite among South Asian international students.\n\n✅ Good To Know\nAt $1,350–$1,550, the rent is among the cheapest of any walk-to-campus property on this list. If your priority is minimising commute time and grocery runs on a student budget, this is a strong match. The single-floor-plan constraint is the main drawback — no flexibility if you want a 1BR or a larger group unit.',
