    "description": "A peaceful, pet-friendly community that leans more scenic and low-key than social, with reliable staff and pricing that stays attractive for shared student housing.\r\n\r\n🏠 The Community\r\nThe Social Amherst has a quieter feel than the name suggests. Residents consistently mention the leasing office and on-site team as one of the property's stronger points, and the setting appeals to renters who want something calmer than a party-oriented complex. The dog park and nearby trail add to that outdoorsy feel.\r\n\r\n💡 What's Included\r\nAvailable layouts include 2 Bed / 1 Bath, 2 Bed / 1.5 Bath, 3 Bed / 1.5 Bath, and 4 Bed / 1.5 Bath apartments. The half-bath options make a noticeable difference for shared living, especially in the larger units. Standard kitchens and parking are included, pets are welcome, and the property has added a dog park with a gym planned or recently introduced depending on timing.\r\n\r\n🚌 Getting Around\r\nThe complex sits about 1.8 mi from UMass on PVTA Route 31, which keeps campus reasonably accessible and also connects toward Amherst College and Hampshire College. The bigger inconvenience is shopping: full grocery runs are awkward without a car, the bus trip toward Hadley is long, and Sunday service is thinner than ideal. That's why residents tend to rate amenities at 3/5 and commute convenience at 2.5/5.\r\n\r\n✅ Good To Know\r\nPer-person costs are among the cheaper options in the area, with living-room setups typically running $400–$600 and private bedrooms usually landing between $550 and $750. Most apartments house two to four people. Satisfaction lands around 4/5, with praise focused on the setting, staff, and campus access, while grocery convenience remains the recurring downside.",
